Class AddressedMessage

Show UML class diagram
  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openlcb.Message
      • org.openlcb.AddressedMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OpenLcb
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DatagramAcknowledgedMessage, DatagramMessage, DatagramRejectedMessage, IdentifyEventsMessage, OptionalIntRejectedMessage, ProtocolIdentificationReplyMessage, ProtocolIdentificationRequestMessage, SimpleNodeIdentInfoReplyMessage, SimpleNodeIdentInfoRequestMessage, StreamDataCompleteMessage, StreamDataProceedMessage, StreamDataSendMessage, StreamInitReplyMessage, StreamInitRequestMessage

    @Immutable
 @ThreadSafe
public abstract class AddressedMessage
extends Message
    Base for addressed OpenLCB message types

    Messages (and therefore all subtypes) are immutable once created.

    A Message works with a MessageDecoder object in a double dispatch pattern to do message specific-processing in e.g. a node implementation.

    See Also:
    MessageDecoder
